{
  "$description": "Caliber (light-only) preset for acuity-dev. A tier-2 semantic overlay on the shared design-kit base (pinned 499fb3a) - it changes token values only, never component structure. Navy core (#072052) on a bright warm-cream field (#FFFEFD), an 8/10/16px boxed-canvas radius scale, narrow-spread navy-tinted soft elevation, Fraunces 600 titles over a system-sans body, IBM Plex Mono accents. Every value is verbatim from docs/design/branding/FINAL.md, which mirrors the ratified acuity-labs ADR 0040/0042 palette; values flagged ink-muted are derived per FINAL.md's auditable-fill convention. Light mode only: dark mode is out of scope for Phase 1 (FINAL.md Dark mode). Applied over the base the same way canvas/dusk/bloom are - the component tier is untouched, so the whole roster re-themes through the semantic CSS-var layer alone.",
  "$preset": {
    "name": "caliber-light",
    "title": "Caliber (light)",
    "summary": "Warm clinical: navy core on bright cream, hairline structure, narrow soft elevation, 8/10/16px radius scale, serif titles - light only.",
    "seed": "#072052"
  },
  "primitive": {
    "color": {
      "$type": "color",
      "caliber": {
        "$description": "The ratified Caliber palette, verbatim from docs/design/branding/FINAL.md (acuity-labs ADR 0040/0042). Neutrals + accents the Caliber semantic roles alias. ink-muted is a derived auditable fill (~5.9:1 on cream, AA normal) since FINAL.md defines no muted-ink value.",
